00:29:55.700 --> 00:29:57.159
--
of deficit.

00:29:57.159 --> 00:30:02.220
So this is a Keynesian bastard, what we're
doing today.

00:30:02.220 --> 00:30:08.890
Our economic policy I describe as a
Keynesian bastard because half of it government

00:30:08.890 --> 00:30:12.379
can run
deficits, we took, can we multiplied it by

00:30:12.379 --> 00:30:17.070
two, which
you know will not get you to the original

00:30:17.070 --> 00:30:18.080
hole.

00:30:18.080 --> 00:30:23.200
So
that's why I think Keynes got some negative

00:30:23.200 --> 00:30:31.570
press is
that he was accused of allowing budget deficits,

00:30:31.570 --> 00:30:36.210
yes,
under conditions that you can run budget surpluses.

00:30:36.210 --> 00:30:40.049
So
we really took half of Keynes and bastardized

00:30:40.049 --> 00:30:45.429
him with
sweet-tooth political populism.

00:30:45.429 --> 00:30:47.940
So that's just the
comment on Keynes.

